Exceptions handling in Java:
Exceptions are unwanted behaviours that disturbs the normal flow of code.
Why Exception handling why not put if else conditions?
1)we can not cover all of the issues by writing if else conditions
2) Exception handling mechanism in java provides us a standard way to find out the issues in our code.
finilize()
This method is called by GC whenever the instance of your class is destroyed to free up class leverl
resources.